abstract: >-
  A validated Python implementation of the Dietary Inflammatory Index (DII)
  for nutritional epidemiology research. This package provides efficient,
  vectorized calculations for assessing the inflammatory potential of
  dietary intake patterns based on the methodology established by
  Shivappa et al. (2014).
